The paper proposes a new topic model that includes a log-linear prior on document-topic distributions based on observed features of the document, such as author, publication venue, references, and dates. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI), as these sub-categories are all relevant to the development and application of topic models.
